==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Breadroot
<hw>Bread`root"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The root of a leguminous plant (<spn>Psoralea esculenta</spn>),
found near the Rocky Mountains. It is usually oval in form, and abounds
in farinaceous matter, affording sweet and palatable food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is the <xex>Pomme blanche</xex> of Canadian
voyageurs.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breadstuff</ent>⟦br⟧
